# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this React + Vite project by following the latest official documentation from Vercel.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Package
- Added `@vercel/speed-insights` version `^2.0.0` to project dependencies
- Used npm to install the package, which updated both `package.json` and `package-lock.json`

### 2. Modified Files

#### `package.json`
- Added `"@vercel/speed-insights": "^2.0.0"` to dependencies

#### `package-lock.json`
- Updated lock file with the new dependency and its 31 transitive dependencies

#### `src/App.tsx`
- Imported `SpeedInsights` component from `@vercel/speed-insights/react`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the App component's JSX
- Wrapped return value in React Fragment to accommodate multiple children

## Implementation Details

### Framework Detection
This project uses React 19.2.7 with Vite 8.1.0 as the build tool. Following the official Vercel documentation, I used the React-specific instructions which require:
1. Importing from `@vercel/speed-insights/react`
2. Adding the `<SpeedInsights />` component to the root component

### Placement
The `SpeedInsights` component was added to `App.tsx` which serves as the main application component. This ensures the Speed Insights tracking is active across the entire application.

## Verification

### Build Status
✅ TypeScript compilation successful
✅ Vite build successful (239ms)
✅ Generated production bundle: 227.75 kB (71.56 kB gzipped)

### Linting
✅ oxlint passed with 0 warnings and 0 errors (20ms on 4 files)

### Tests
No test suite configured in the project (no test script in package.json)

## Next Steps for Deployment

To enable Speed Insights in production:
1. Deploy this application to Vercel
2. Navigate to the Speed Insights tab in the Vercel dashboard
3. Select your project and click "Enable"
4. Speed Insights will begin collecting performance metrics after the next deployment

## Additional Notes
- The implementation preserves all existing code structure
- No breaking changes were introduced
- The SpeedInsights component is lightweight and has minimal performance impact
- Speed Insights data will only be collected when the app is deployed to Vercel
